Just a heads-up: I'm implementing a boot system. Basic idea is that in VAB you can select the boot file via a tweakable (any Archive file starting with "boot") and it will be copied to Volume 1 upon ship creation with the name "boot". At processor startup, if a file named "boot" exists, it will be executed.

I'll ship two super-trivial boot files, a "standard" one that just prints the standard startup message, and an "auto launch" one that merely turns on SAS and STAGEs - that should get users going with the idea of boot files.

The principle is to allow the player to develop a collection of "standard" file packages, launchers, etc., and select which of those to boot for each ship. Typically they'd in PRELAUNCH copy some files from the Archive and run one while in other boot states do nothing.

Work is mostly done, I'll send a patch soon, but also happy to here any input.

I think we are talking past each other. There aren't any mods installed other than kOS. The only thing I do is assemble a rocket in the VAB and play around with the kOS terminal on the launch pad a bit.

This is what I did (so you can re-produce the issue, maybe ):

I recently downloaded KSP 23.5 from the store website, unzipped it and used the settings.cfg file from KSP 23.0 to import my game settings. This worked with the last few updates so I think copying the settings.cfg doesn't cause problems. Then I downloaded kOSv0.12.1 from the Curse website and unzipped it into the GameData folder.

Then I start up KSP and load the sandbox save with the meaningful name "slihiuhdg" (it's just for testing stuff). In the VAB I build a rocket consisting of a RC-001S pod with a kOS module and a Mk15 parachute on top of it, a FL-T400 fuel tank and LV-T45 engine under it, and a Launch clamp attached to the fuel tank's side. "Open kOS terminal" is bound to action group 1 and "engine shutdown" & "deploy chute" to action group abort. Engine, launch clamp and parachute are each in separate stages.

This is the exact configuration I used.

Then I bring the rocket to the launch pad and open the terminal via the action group. Since file editing is deactivated I use single line commands to play with the rocket. The code I enter line by line is this one:


stage.
lock throttle to 9.81*mass/maxthrust*0.995.

Then I press spacebar to release the launch clamp.

This makes the rocket hover above ground more or less, slowly drifting left and up. When the fuel is about a third down the rocket is quite high above the launch pad, I press the abort button which deactivates the engines and makes the parachute deploy. Since it's too small to land the rocket softly the engine and the fuel tank explode on touchdown. When I now press ESC and select Revert to launch the kOS part appears on the launch pad, floating lonely. All other parts are gone, but the kOS part is where it should be if all other parts were present. Now I can't open the terminal anymore, the stage are gone and key entries seem not to do anything. The ESC key seems to be the only key working and I switch to the Space Center. But now I can't enter any building here nor get back to the launch pad or the main menu. The only way out I found was closing the window using ALT-F4 (or pressing X) and restarting the game.

It's re-productive. So any time I do the above, which is in it's core having a rocket with a kOS part (from the VAB, not a part module) and reverting the flight to either the VAB or the launch pad, I get the same results as described above.
